def parse_date(row):
    return du.parser.parse(row['date'])
In[4]:
def process_lib(lib):
    name = lib['name']
    if not os.path.exists(f'{name}.csv'):
        print(f'File {name}.csv not found.')
        return

    df = pd.read_csv(f'{name}.csv', sep='|')

    # Convert date to datetime format
    df['date'] = df.apply(parse_date, axis=1)

    # Drop rows where date could not be parsed
    df = df.dropna(subset=['date'])

    # Convert numeric columns
    df[['typesCount', 'methodsCount', 'fieldsCount', 'breakingChangesCount', 'deprecatedAnnotationsCount', 'betaAnnotationsCount']] = df[
        ['typesCount', 'methodsCount', 'fieldsCount', 'breakingChangesCount', 'deprecatedAnnotationsCount', 'betaAnnotationsCount']].apply(pd.to_numeric)

    # Versions and their release dates
    versions = lib['versions']
    version_dates = {k: pd.to_datetime(v) for k, v in versions.items()}

    # Combined plot for API size and breaking changes
    fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 5))
    fig.suptitle(f"{name} API Symbols and Breaking Changes", fontsize=14)

    df['apiSymbolsCount'] = df['typesCount'] + df['methodsCount'] + df['fieldsCount']

    # Plot API size evolution
    ax1.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax1.set_ylabel('Symbols Count', color='tab:blue')
    ax1.plot(df['date'], df['apiSymbolsCount'], label='API Symbols', color='tab:blue')
    ax1.plot(df['date'], df['deprecatedAnnotationsCount'], label='Deprecated Symbols', color='tab:green')
    ax1.plot(df['date'], df['betaAnnotationsCount'], label='Beta Symbols', color='tab:orange')
    ax1.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor='tab:blue')
    ax1.legend(loc='center right', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0.6))
    ax1.grid(True)

    formatted_data_for_bc = df[['date', 'breakingChangesCount']].copy()
    i = 0
    while i < len(formatted_data_for_bc):
        if formatted_data_for_bc['breakingChangesCount'][i] > 0:
            date = formatted_data_for_bc['date'][i]
            date_minus_one = date - datetime.timedelta(seconds=1)
            date_plus_one = date + datetime.timedelta(seconds=1)

            before_line = pd.DataFrame({'date': date_minus_one, 'breakingChangesCount': 0}, index=[i - 1])
            line = pd.DataFrame({'date': date, 'breakingChangesCount': formatted_data_for_bc['breakingChangesCount'][i]}, index=[i])
            after_line = pd.DataFrame({'date': date_plus_one, 'breakingChangesCount': 0}, index=[i + 1])

            formatted_data_for_bc = pd.concat([formatted_data_for_bc.iloc[:i], before_line, line, after_line, formatted_data_for_bc.iloc[i+1:]]).reset_index(drop=True)

            i += 3
        else:
            i += 1

    # Create second y-axis for breaking changes
    ax2 = ax1.twinx()
    ax2.set_ylabel('Breaking Changes Count', color='tab:red')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='breakingChangesCount', data=formatted_data_for_bc, color='tab:red', ax=ax2)
    ax2.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor='tab:red')
    ax2.legend(['Breaking Changes'], loc='center right', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0.45))
    ax2.grid(False)

    ax1.set_facecolor('#0000')
    ax2.set_facecolor('#0000')

    # Add version release dates as vertical lines
    for version, vdate in version_dates.items():
        ax1.axvline(vdate, color='gray', linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)
        ax1.text(vdate, ax1.get_ylim()[1] * 0.9, version, rotation=90, verticalalignment='top', fontsize=9, color='gray')

    plt.show()
    fig.savefig(f'{name}_api_information.pdf', bbox_inches='tight')
